channel.title: [PI] Webclient Problem
channel.description:
:confused:[size=36pt]WEBCLIENT PROBLEM[/size] :confused:
[size=18pt]Problems:[/size] -Webclient is on website, yet both the client on computer, and webclient won't work -webclient says = "Sorry, an error has occurred whilst loading Runescape: -try reloading browser - try using different java - try a different world - etc...
client on computer says : connection error - retrying in [] seconds
and keeps going on from there.
[size=24pt]WHAT I DID DO:[/size] -Put the cache with sprites, raw, and data folders and all the other files, (not the cache folder itself, but all the files in it) up for download at fileden. -took the link from fileden and put it in cachedownloader.java -put name of cache in class36.java -put name of cache in modeldecompressor.java -put name of cache in sprite.java ----pictures on bottom for those ------
I also looked up several tutorials and looked for help but couldn't find it!
I have tried several methods but none work!
also, i forgot to mention: [size=36pt]I AM A NOVICE PROGRAMMER, IF ANYTHING, so please be detailed with your responses![/size]
---------my skype is drew.wilken------------
--------I can teamviewer you if you would like, just talk to me in skype and tell me your info on that...-------
